abs} requires the existence of a correlation between\n\\Sigma and the central activity. An increase of typical values of \\Sigma with\nz, correlated with the activity, might explain an increase of f_{abs} with z.\nHowever, at the highest luminosities f_{abs} could hardly exceed about 0.3.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 May 2008 09:16:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 4 Jun 2008 14:02:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
